Mali Floods Destroy 1,750 Homes, Kill Animals, Ministries Say

-- B y   D i a k a r i d i a   D e m b e l e
-- 
2011-08-29T14:34:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-29/mali-floods-destroy-1-750-homes-kill-animals-ministries-say.html
Floods caused by heavy rainfall in
 Mali  destroyed 1,750 homes and have affected 14,300 residents
of Gossi, a town in the northeast, two government ministries
said today.  More than 1,000 animals were killed and agricultural
fields destroyed when about 120 millimeters (4.7 inches) of
rain fell on Aug. 20, according to an e-mailed statement sent
today from Harouna Cisse, minister of social development and
Sadio Gassama, minister of internal security and civil
protection.  The West African nation sent 20 million  CFA francs 
($44,000) and 121 metric tons of cereal to the area, the
statement from the Bamako-based ministries said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Diakaridia Dembele in Bamako via Accra at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at  asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 